{
  "texts": [
    "Results from the calibration curve, ROC analysis, and DCA collectively demonstrated the nomogram's performance and suitability for clinical application, with areas under the ROC curve exceeding 0.800 for 3-, 5-, and 10-year intervals.",
    "Zhang et al.",
    "71 presented the progression of five models is detailed sequentially, starting with label information that involves categorical encoding of both drugs and cell lines.",
    "Subsequent steps include incorporating the chemical structure of drugs encoded by molecular fingerprints and cell line cancer gene expression.",
    "Further enhancements involve the addition of monotherapy efficacy, followed by the incorporation of dose-response curve baseline features and imputation features."
  ]
}